As a lover of everything animation and parkour, this game was made for me. Levels are well crafted, and require precise inputs to be completed with three stars. Restarting a level is thankfully quick and easy, something games like this need. And the graphics are fast and fluid. Except when they aren't. This game is plagued by some of the worst slowdown I have ever seen. I have a european, quad core HTC One X, and this is the ONLY game (including heavy 3D games) I have found to slow my phone down. And we're not talking slight slowdown. We are talking 30%-50% speed, slow motion gameplay, usually on the longer stages. Turning off power saving speeds it up somewhat, but not nearly enough. I wish the developers could iron out these "bugs", or program it better. As of now, it is anything but optimized. Check out the free version first, and play all the way to 1-11 (where it really slows down for me) to see how your phone does.

Other than that all I can say is that it's a fantastic new take on Canabalt!
